article.description: Bryce Douvier scored 10 points, including a pair of free throws to give Texas A&M-Corpus Christi the lead for good in a 51-48 win over Sam Houston State on Saturday night.
article.headline: Texas A&M-CC beats Sam Houston , 51-48; now tied for 2nd
article.linkText: Texas A&M-CC beats Sam Houston , 51-48; now tied for 2nd
article.story: HOUSTON -- Bryce Douvier scored 10 points, including a pair of free throws to give Texas A&M-Corpus Christi the lead for good in a 51-48 win over Sam Houston State on Saturday night. The Islanders move into a second-place tie with Houston Baptist, two games back of undefeated Stephen F. Austin in the Southland Conference standings. Josh Delaney hit a 3-pointer to pull Sam Houston State to 47-46, and Dakarai Henderson converted a pair of free throws to put the Bearkats in the lead, 48-47 with 3:05 to play. But Sam Houston State did not score again. Bouvier drew a foul from Albert Almanza and hit both free throws with 2:09 left. Jelani Currie got to the basket for a layup with 32 seconds for the final margin. Texas A&M-CC (17-5, 8-2) was 21 of 61 from the field (34.4 percent). Henderson scored 20 points for Sam Houston State (12-12, 7-4).
